Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at the 45th Space Wing, praising the men and women of the United States Space Force and thanking them for their service. He also mentioned the passing of General Chuck Yeager and announced that future Space Force bases will be named in his honor. Pence highlighted President Trump's leadership in establishing the Space Force and commended General Jay Raymond for his role as Chief of Space Operations. He emphasized the importance of space security and the need to defend the nation and its freedom in space. Pence announced that Cape Canaveral Air Force Station will now become Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, and Patrick Air Force Base will become Patrick Space Force Base. He expressed confidence that the Space Force will continue to defend the nation from these bases for generations to come. Pence concluded by thanking the military personnel for their service and urging them to continue making America safe and secure.